The defendant Darius Emanuel Eddmonds was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of THC (2nd+ Offense), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Darius Emanuel Eddmonds in court with attorney Melissa Nepomiachi.  Paul Michael Hauer appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Sentencing proceeded.  State makes no corrections to the Presentence Report.  Defense puts changes to the Presentence Report on the record.   Statements made by State, Defense and Defendant.  The Court sentenced defendant to serve 30 DAYS, straight time, with good time credit, in the House of Corrections, with credit for 4 days time served.  

-Court ordered defendant pay a fine in the amount of $2,000.00 PLUS Court costs and all applicable surcharges and assessments by applying cash bail on deposit; any remaining balance penalty shall result in a civil judgment

  Plea hearing proceeded. Negotiations placed on the record and confirmed by defense counsel and defendant.
AS TO COUNT 1 :

The defendant was advised of his Constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, Jury Instructions and Addendum to Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights received and filed.  The parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  The Court found the defendant guilty and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.

Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions:  Firearm possession and Voting. Defendant further advised that if he is not a US citizen deportation is possible. 

Court ordered a presentence investigation without a recommendation.  Order for presentence investigation signed and filed. 

Parties advised the Court will listen to statements by counsel, any victims, and the defendant. Any other statements must be in writing and provided to the Court 3 business days in advance of the sentencing. 

Case adjourned for PSI sentencing hearing on 03-17-2016 at 8:30, branch 17.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for March 17, 2016 at 08:30 am.
